$0.80 Earnings Per Share Expected for Steris Plc (STE) This Quarter


					Posted by Oliver Carreras on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments




Analysts expect Steris Plc (NYSE:STE) to post earnings per share of $0.80 for the current fiscal quarter, according to Zacks. Three analysts have provided estimates for Steris Plc’s earnings, with the highest EPS estimate coming in at $0.82 and the lowest estimate coming in at $0.78. Steris Plc posted earnings of $0.79 per share during the same quarter last year, which would indicate a positive year over year growth rate of 1.3%. The firm is scheduled to announce its next earnings report  on Tuesday, August 8th.
According to Zacks, analysts expect that Steris Plc will report full-year earnings of $4.06 per share for the current financial year, with EPS estimates ranging from $4.05 to $4.08. For the next financial year, analysts expect that the business will report earnings of $4.53 per share, with EPS estimates ranging from $4.51 to $4.57. Zacks Investment Research’s earnings per share calculations are a mean average based on a survey of research analysts that follow Steris Plc.


 Get Steris Plc alerts:



Steris Plc (NYSE:STE) last announced its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May 9th. The medical equipment provider reported $1.11 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $1.07 by $0.04. The firm had revenue of $681.20 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $673.47 million. Steris Plc had a return on equity of 11.12% and a net margin of 4.20%. The firm’s quarterly revenue was down 1.3% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the prior year, the company posted $0.90 earnings per share. 





STE has been the subject of a number of analyst reports. Zacks Investment Research upgraded Steris Plc from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report on Wednesday, March 22nd. Wellington Shields lowered Steris Plc from a “gradually accumulate” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report on Monday, June 5th. Finally, KeyCorp upgraded Steris Plc from a “sector weight” rating to an “overweight” rating and set a $89.00 price target for the company in a research report on Wednesday, May 3rd. Two analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and three have given a buy rating to the company. Steris Plc currently has an average rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $84.00.
Steris Plc (STE) opened at 81.91 on Wednesday. Steris Plc has a one year low of $63.80 and a one year high of $83.54. The company has a 50-day moving average price of $81.05 and a 200-day moving average price of $73.40. The firm has a market capitalization of $6.96 billion, a P/E ratio of 63.99 and a beta of 1.33. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Thursday, June 29th. Shareholders of record on Wednesday, June 7th were given a dividend of $0.28 per share. The ex-dividend date  was Monday, June 5th. This represents a $1.12 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 1.37%. Steris Plc’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 87.50%. 
In other news, CFO Michael J. Tokich sold 13,600 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction on Tuesday, May 9th. The stock was sold at an average price of $76.00, for a total value of $1,033,600.00. Following the sale, the chief financial officer now owns 58,106 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $4,416,056. The transaction was disclosed in a document filed with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through this link. Also, Director Michael B. Wood sold 4,000 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction on Monday, July 3rd. The stock was sold at an average price of $81.50, for a total value of $326,000.00. Following the completion of the sale, the director now directly owns 26,131 shares in the company, valued at approximately $2,129,676.50. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders sold a total of 60,880 shares of company stock worth $4,738,494 in the last three months. Company insiders own  2.55% of the company’s stock. 
Hedge funds have recently bought and sold shares of the company. Louisiana State Employees Retirement System increased its stake in  Steris Plc by 1.4% in the first quarter. Louisiana State Employees Retirement System now owns 21,400 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock worth $1,486,000 after buying an additional 300 shares in the last quarter.  Norges Bank purchased a new stake in  Steris Plc during the fourth quarter worth approximately $45,178,000.  Russell Investments Group Ltd. increased its stake in  Steris Plc by 57.5% in the first quarter. Russell Investments Group Ltd. now owns 132,035 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock worth $9,171,000 after buying an additional 48,188 shares in the last quarter.  Washington Capital Management Inc. increased its stake in  Steris Plc by 35.6% in the first quarter. Washington Capital Management Inc. now owns 8,000 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock worth $556,000 after buying an additional 2,100 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Bragg Financial Advisors Inc purchased a new stake in  Steris Plc during the first quarter worth approximately $1,159,000. 90.43% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 
