STERIS Corp NYSE:STE Company Profile

STERIS Corporation (STERIS) is a provider of infection prevention and other procedural products and services, focused primarily on healthcare, pharmaceutical and research. The Company operates in three segments: Healthcare, Life Sciences, and STERIS Isomedix Services. The Healthcare segment manufactures and sells capital equipment, accessory, consumables, information support and service solutions to healthcare providers, including acute care hospitals and surgery and gastrointestinal (GI) centers. The Life Sciences segment manufactures and sells a range of capital equipment, formulated cleaning chemistries, and service solutions to pharmaceutical companies and private and public research facilities. The Isomedix segment sells an array of contract processing services, as well as laboratory testing services. It offers microbial reduction services based on Customer specifications to companies that supply products to the healthcare, industrial, and consumer product industries.
Company Website: STERIS Corp
 Steris Corp was filled in Ohio on 1985-08-09. At the moment its market worth is: $4.05 billion and it has 58.87 million shares outstanding. This company has 7600 employees. Today the company has 108.12% shareholders and the institutional ownership is 108.12%. The stock closed at $68.800003 yesterday and it had average 2 days volume of 225334 shares. It is up from the 30 days average shares volume of 208333. Steris Corp has a 52 weeks low of $59.11 and a 52w high of $71.33. The current price is above the 200 days SMA. Steris Corp last issued its quarterly earnings information on 08/04/2015. The company reported 0.62 EPS for the quarter, above the consensus estimate of 0.6 by 0.02. The company had a revenue of 439.90 million for 6/30/2015 and 501.65 million for 3/31/2015. Therefore, the revenue was -61,745,000 down.
